        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down,| Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Dec 5. ’72</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I am much obliged for Your note &amp; reference, but hardly know what to think of this statement about the Watering mouth.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Dear Sir | Yours faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">In <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref>, pp. 75, 341, 344, CD had referred to increased salivation in the case of a hungry man faced with tempting food, and by the thought and taste of sour fruit.</note>
        </div>                
